tip.text: Amazing coffee shop & retail concept. Unique and quite a pleasant surprise to find in quaint & sleepy Pescadero. Great way to top up a meal from Duarte's across the street.
My neighborhood coffee shop, restaurant, bar. Great atmosphere! Friendly people, good menus from breakfast, lunch & dinner or anytime in between. Will try the cocktails sometime.

formattedAddress: 501 Stanyan St (btwn Fulton St & Lincoln Way)

contact.facebookName: San Francisco Recreation and Park Department

tip.text: All I can say-chilled artichoke w/aioli, a bowl of artichoke cream soup and another bowl of green chili cream soup (mix together or savor by mixed spoonfuls) and the unique ollallie pie ala mode!
Awesome architecture outside & inside. Very well curated collection of contemporary art. Only downside is the no photo of art policy. Quite surprising it applies even to their permanent exhibitions.
Beautiful boutique hotel, located a bit off the center, more residential area.  The rooms are well appointed & the best part is the comp breakfast! Six stars!

formattedAddress: Av de Ategorrieta 61 20013 San SebastiÃ¡n Spain

tip.text: Old industrial building converted into an entertainment & sports complex. Interesting architecture, notice the one of a kind pillars and yes, the glass swimming pool above your head.
Star attraction is the Franco era stainglass window
Pretty authentic pho. Cute little restaurant, very democratic prices, can get busy you might have to wait for a table.
Must visit regardless you're a tourist or not. Beautiful complex, a pleasure to stroll around.
Retro kitschy interiors with (obviously) chicken motif! The chicken soup is delicious, just like grandma's. I would come back just for this. And chicken Kyiv served many different ways.
Big complex of churches varying from ancient to modern architecture. Very good religious & handicraft store in the premises with good prices.

venue.name: Mother See of Holy Etchmiadzin | Մայր Աթոռ Սուրբ Էջմիածին

tip.text: A 7th century Armenian Apostolic Church. Don't miss the remains of ancient murals on the left side of the entrance.

venue.name: St. Gayane Holy Church | Սուրբ Գայանե եկեղեցի

tip.text: One of the highlights of my visit! World class live jazz with excellent Armenian cuisine, wines & liquor. I suggest you stay till closing to fully enjoy the excellent lineup of jazz artists.
One of the best point to view Mt. Ararat in it's glory. If you come here on a bright clear day, you are blessed, guaranteed the best photo op.
UNESCO World Heritage Site. Stunning Medieval complex with a church carved out of the adjacent mountain. Amazing views, tranquil, holy place. A must see.
Free! Museum, gallery, passage. Amazing collection of world renowned contemporary artists. Unique way to enjoy art-while on escalators. Don't miss the hidden rooms. So much to see inside & outdoors.

contact.facebookName: Cafesjian Center for the Arts (Cascade complex)

venue.name: Cafesjian Center for the Arts | Գաֆէսճեան արվեստի կենտրոն

tip.text: Beer crafted in the premises! The  burger is perfect. Kinda ironic to indulge in beer in a place steeped in history of wine & cognac making, but hey variety is the spice of life!
What a lovely walking town! People are friendly & I was surprised English is spoken widely. So much history and the unique architecture is amazing. Surprises await while you meander the streets.
Very interesting museum dedicated to the development of Theatre in Ukraine. It's tucked in a quiet corner in the Lavra complex. What a gem!

venue.name: Державний музей театрального, музичного та кіномистецтва України

tip.text: A very fancy & expansive tasting room with modern vibe. Unique selection of Starbucks merchandise and more. Quite touristy, but I have to say I had my best Starbucks coffee here.

contact.facebookName: Starbucks Reserve Roastery and Tasting Room

tip.text: One of the most unique museums I've been to, must see!
Lucked out on the weather & enjoyed a leisurely stroll on the waterfront. Beautiful!
Had deliciously prepared crab here picked from the fresh seafood store next door. Delilah!
FRESH & tasty. Will deliver anywhere in the US of A. Or they'll pack it for you to take on the plane. Generous tasting policy before you buy.
My favorite destination in Seattle! Fresh seafood, gourmet meals, artisan bake shops, cheese, chowder, handicrafts & more! I can spend days exploring this placel
Second time around and still impressed with the quality of the seafood & cooking. Happy hour starts at 3pm with a special drinks menu & 5-6 dishes of tapas style snacks.
Stumbled upon the church right in the middle of Seattle. Located on an old high rise with unique modern architecture.

venue.name: St. Catherine's of Alexandria Catholic Church

tip.text: New, looks well marketed with the number of people wine tasting. Wines were ok but quite pricy and the bread wine pairing did not do it for me. Regardless, fun place to go for the space & atmosphere
The octopus seaweed & cucumber salad is ok. The Khao Soi disappointing-too thick, I suspect the sauce came from a box 😔. Friendly service though & big portions. Maybe best to order the sautéed items,
Long winding beach lined with cafes, beach sport equipment, cafe's & restaurant. Great beach to hangout, jog, workout & chill.
Farmer's market & food court open on Saturdays. A bit of a distance from the center of the city, but worth a visit.
Hotel right on the beach with direct access to the constantly evolving TelAviv seafront. Fantastic ocean views & terraces. Friendly staff, comfy rooms. Good executive lounge, open everyday.
I preferred it when it was Nebos. Last visit, the service was spotty. My friend was served all the dishes he ordered, while mine arrived minutes after he finished. I was ready to leave. Dish just ok.
Compact but beautifully designed spa. The massage/champagne package is a great way to relax after a full day of exploring Lviv.
Excellent coffee shop in a tranquil wooden complex slightly off the main drag of busy Laguna beach. Great to sit outdoors to enjoy the 'forest' atmosphere.
Very California carefree, bohemian beach scene. Fun to walk around & hang on the beach on the sunny day.
Excellent oysters, mussels (pictured), grilled artichoke & calamari. Great vibe, friendly people.

location.crossStreet: btw E. Main St. & E. Santa Clara St.
formattedAddress: 60 California St. (btw E. Main St. & E. Santa Clara St.)

tip.text: Authentic Wild West with hearty cuisine. Best to come hungry. Live music in the evenings. Friendly service. Atmospheric & do walk around the restaurant. Wear your cowboy boots!
Don't miss if you're in the area! It's like going back in time of the Wild West! Fun to walk around both day & night. Good restaurants & a real cowboy restaurant.
Enjoy delicious lunch prepared in the winery kitchen while you taste the wines on offer. Wine tasting is free with lunch order. Takes wine tasting to a new level!👍

Modern,bright interiors,efficient service and the food? Specifically the seafood is delicious,from the chillicrabs,salt & pepper prawns,steamed fresh fish etc.The Sichuan green beans were exceptional!
Views! Date shake, ahi tuna burger & sweet-potato fries! Enough said.
Fantastic ocean front community. More special in the holiday season when a lot of the houses are dressed up to the occasion. Fun to visit both day& night.
Lots of history, restored cottages & small gardens. A great way to break the hike in the area. Great restaurants too!
Good first intro to hiking. Drink lots of water, walk at your own pace & enjoy the view!

formattedAddress: 8471 N Coast Hwy (in Crystal Cove State Park)

tip.text: Breathtaking views with a few drinks before dinner. Service was a bit flustered last time I was there, but regardless the view made up for it.
Celebrated New Year's Eve here & it was an excellent choice. The food, service & atmosphere lived up to the occasion! Highly recommended.

formattedAddress: 235 N Canon Dr (at Dayton and Clifton)

tip.text: Good wines, friendly staff who know their stuff, beautiful grounds highlighted by sculptures (Sculpterra 😉). Definitely a must visit when you're on the wine trail.
So retro, hailing from the 50's with so much history! A real piece of Americana! Fun & good seafood.
Bone in Fillet, with creamed potatoes & sautéed spinach, topped with butter cake & coffee for dessert-is decadence!
When the main courses arrived, everyone was pleased. The seafood pasta was exceptional! And the portions were huge!

formattedAddress: 8471 N Coast Hwy (in Crystal Cove State Park)

tip.text: Literally farm to table! Excellent mixed salad, fresh home made pastas, pizza etc. Every dish in the menu is delicious! Excellent house ice cream too!

formattedAddress: 23407 San José del Cabo, Baja California Sur

tip.text: Sprawling grounds with high ceiling expansive rooms most with water views. Modern design but not very senior or handicap friendly due to multi-level architecture-lots of going up & down stairs.

location.address: Fraccion Hotelera FH5-C1, Subdelegacion de la Playita Puerto Los Cabos
formattedAddress: Fraccion Hotelera FH5-C1, Subdelegacion de la Playita Puerto Los Cabos
23403 San José del Cabo, Baja California Sur

tip.text: Modern take on Mexican cuisine. The pulpo, prawn & fish dishes were exceptional. Also interesting tacos & leave room for the chocolate pot-best shared!
Good seafood, huge portions. Grilled artichoke exceptional!
Scenic area by the beach with boardwalk, resort shops & eclectic restaurants. Vibrant nightlife. Beautiful sunset!
What a fun place! Club, lounge, theatre & restaurant in one place. Best to keep track of scheduled performers & book early to reserve best tables.
Re-opened Tsum. Modern interiors, high potential to be the prime dept. store in the city. Good perfume & cosmetic selection, excellent one stop venue for international & up market Ukrainian brands.
Great location for downtown touring or for work in the financial district. Intimate lobby, great views of the city & the Hudson.
Beautiful modern interiors. Very good Italian cuisine, most memorable were the perfectly aldente homemade pasta dishes and the grilled octopus with chickpeas 😘. Good wine selection.

venue.name: Tapping Reeve House And Law School

tip.text: Pub with modern Asian twist. Nice atmosphere, friendly service. And surprisingly the curry was pretty authentic, home style.
Highlight Venetian cuisine. I specially like the cicchetti (Venetian take on tapas), the fresh pasta and the meat dishes. Very good wine selection as well.
Ultra modern interiors in an iconic building. Stunning lobby. Wonderful bar lounge facing the river.

formattedAddress: 330 N Wabash Ave (At the Chicago River)

tip.text: Touristy but always fun to go for a drink to enjoy the city views on a clear day.

formattedAddress: 875 N Michigan Ave (btwn Delaware Pl & Chestnut St)

tip.text: Speakeasy with vintage ambiance. Interesting tarot cards cocktail menu and entertaining burlesque shows. Good night out.
Historic pub/bar with a good wine & spirits shop. Very atmospheric.
Speakeasy bar with live jazz. My current favorite after dinner spot to chill. Not easy to locate, but try hard enough you will not be disappointed! Extensive & very good cocktail & drinks menu.
Recently modernized after Carlsberg took over. Stunning modern reception area. Interesting beer tour.
Fantastic new addition to the cafe scene in Lviv. One of the best run cat themed coffee shops I've been to. Delicious pastries and savories. Convenient tram ride away from Rynok Square.
One of the many architectural gem in Rynok Square. Wonderful place for a cup of coffee or tea. Very atmospheric.
Delightful place specializing in gingerbread cookies decorated in many ways! Great area for children to decorate their own. Cute coffee shop in the back to relax and enjoy the cookies
Friendly place, good coffee and my favorite place to sit is on the stools facing the glass windows.
Very good  acoustic, elegant & almost intimate venue.

venue.name: National Philharmonic of Ukraine (Національна філармонія України)

tip.text: Great views. Friendly staff. Good drinks selection, but the food selection did not vary much, so not too good for extended stays.
Great views good food.
Beautiful beach with skyline views of Chicago across the lake. Another great day trip from Chicago.
Dollar oysters happy hour! Fun friendly and satisfying Japanese fare.
A Chicago institution. Really talented musicians & performers. If you like jazz, this is the place. I like the way they switch stage & performers in different rooms.
One of the best quality ice cream I've had! Unique flavors, brilliant combinations. A must stop every time I'm in the area.

formattedAddress: 1505 N Milwaukee Ave (at N Honore St)

tip.text: My favorite brunch place in Geneva IL! Lots of healthy & hearty choices. Buttermilk biscuits! And be mindful the kitchen stops at 2:30pm!
Love this place! Big group, family friendly! As close as you can get to Munich Octoberfest experience in Chicago. Excellent beer & authentic German cuisine.

location.crossStreet: btwn Bryn Mawr Ave & Balmoral Ave
formattedAddress: 5500 Park Pl (btwn Bryn Mawr Ave & Balmoral Ave)

tip.text: Very good salads, pork knuckle dish was delicious (best to share), burgers good and leave space for dessert! Only down side, service can be spotty.

formattedAddress: 671 N. St. Clair (Erie and N. St. Clair)

tip.text: Fantastic views, pretty good food & service. Highlight for me is the stunning view from the terrace. Book a table right next to the window.
Ready wear or custom made clothes. Simple classic designs, Sewn by twin brothers.
Excellent Cuban cuisine & great atmospheric venue, sassy waitresses. Don't miss!
Follow up to my recent tip, as slow as the start might have been, the food was as good as I remember. Local veal is fantastic. The veal ribs with grilled veggies were delicious! 😘

formattedAddress: вул. Павла Грабовського, 11 (вул. Академика Філарета Колесси)

tip.text: Had high expectations since my last visit, but this time it was disappointing! Service was sloooow, and restaurant was not even full! Had to approach these guys to get my order. Hope food is better.

formattedAddress: вул. Павла Грабовського, 11 (вул. Академика Філарета Колесси)

tip.text: Impressive bourbon selection, great atmosphere & very knowledgeable bar man.
Delicious hearty salads. Okay service, nice atmosphere especially when seated by the opened Windows.

formattedAddress: 100 E Walton St (at N Michigan Ave)

tip.text: Seriously stocked bourbon bar! A great place to sample to figure out your bourbon fancy. A must stop as you do the bourbon trail.
Good burgers served in different ways, matched with an extensive selection of artisanal beers and serious selection of bourbon.
One of the best bourbon tours in Kentucky (and it's free!) with tastings at the end. Excellent shop too.
Fine restaurant with a very creative kitchen. Best to go with a group to enjoy more of the dishes enjoyed tapas style.
My my favorite  Chinese restaurant in Cincinnati. Love the spicy fried fish, steamed fish-practically everything in the menu! Authentic!
In the mood for Italian? This hits the spot. Good pastas, portions are big though, best to share.
It's sibling restaurant Upstate seem to get more attention, but prefer the space & atmosphere here. Friendly service & excellent seafood. And good selection of beer on tap.
Beautiful Gothic Church in Mayfair located in the Mount Street Gardens.
French cuisine at its finest! A real treat to the senses! Amazing food. An intimate & elegant restaurant with outdoor seating in the summer.
Excellent pub with good selection of beer on tap. Outdoor seating ideal in the summer. Food is good too. Also a more quiet & formal coffee/tearoom towards the back of the pub.
